"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-showbiz-tom-daley-im-a-celebrity-contestant-retirement-diving-paris-olympics-b1176219.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Showbiz  The Standard's journalism is supported by our readers. When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.  Sign up to our free weekly newsletter for exclusive competitions, offers and theatre ticket deals    I would like to be emailed about offers, event and updates from Evening Standard. Read ourprivacy notice.  Tom Daley's odds to take part in the next series of I am A Celebrity... Get Me Out Of Here have shot up after heconfirmed his retirement from divingafter competing at the 2024Olympics.  The 30-year-old athlete made his Olympics debut aged just 14 at the Beijing Games in 2008 and 16 years later has he won a silver medal at the\\u00a0Paris\\u00a0Games to add to his collection of three bronzes and one gold.  After confirming on Mondaythat he will be hanging up his speedos,entering the Australian jungle could be a next step.  The latest odds from Ladbrokes certainly agree, placing him at\\u00a0just 3/1 to appear on the next series when it returns in November hosted by Ant and Dec.  A number of other former Olympians have given it a go over the years, including Sam Quek and Amir Khan.  Daley is also no stranger himself to reality TV after serving as a mentor on ITV show Splash from 2013-2014 where he attempted to teachcelebritieshow to dive.  Addressing his decision to make Paris his last Olympics, Daley toldBritish Vogue: \\\"It feels very, very surreal. I felt so incredibly nervous going into this, knowing it was my last Olympics.  \\\"There was a lot of pressure and expectation. I was eager for it to be done\\u2026 but when I walked out, and saw my husband [Dustin Lance Black] and kids [Robbie and Phoenix] and my friends and family in the audience, I was like, you know what? This is exactly why I did this,\\\" he continued.  \\\"I am here, and no matter what happens in the competition itself, I am going to be happy.  \\\"It was emotional at the end, up there on the platform, knowing it was going to be my last competitive dive.  \\\"But I have to make the decision at some point, and it feels like the right time. It's the right time to call it a day.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"